<sect>Manifest<p>
The following list details the files installed with &mgv;, all of these
paths are relative the the <em>prefix</em> that was given to <tt/configure/
when you built &mgv;.
<descrip>
<tag><tt>bin/mgv</tt></tag>
	The &mgv; executable.
<p><tag><tt>share/mgv/&VERSION;/MGv.gz</tt></tag>
	Application defaults file for &mgv;.  This file is for reference
	purposes only, &mgv; does not read this file.
<p><tag><tt>share/mgv/&VERSION;/README</tt></tag>
	A short description of the files in <tt>share/mgv/4.0.0</tt>.
<p><tag><tt>share/mgv/&VERSION;/help/*</tt></tag>
	HTML and PNG files for the on-line help.
<p><tag><tt>share/mgv/&VERSION;/icon-images.tar.gz</tt></tag>
	The icons, in XPM and XBM formats, used by &mgv;.
<p><tag><tt>share/mgv/&VERSION;/splash-images.tar.gz</tt></tag>
	The splash screens, in XPM and XBM formats, used by &mgv;.
<p><tag><tt>share/mgv/&VERSION;/toolbar-images.tar.gz</tt></tag>
	The toolbar icons, in XPM and XBM formats, used by &mgv;.
</descrip>
If you don't care about on-line help, then the &mgv; executable can be
considered self contained.

<p>The following files are user specific:
<descrip>
<tag><tt>&tilde;/.mgv/resources</tt></tag>
	Stored resources from the last time you ran &mgv;.  You can remove
	this file to restore the default settings.
<p><tag><tt>&tilde;/.mgv/user</tt></tag>
	Various user resources.  &mgv; only reads this file, &mgv; will never
	write to this file.
<p><tag><tt>&tilde;/.mgv/MGv.tmp.*</tt></tag>
	Temporary directories.  These directories should only exist while
	&mgv; is running.
</descrip>

